# Design Instructions

These rules apply to every page and component. Follow them unless the user explicitly says otherwise.

---

## Icons
- Use **Lucide React** only — no Heroicons, no FontAwesome.
- Import from `lucide-react`:
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Bell, Home } from "lucide-react"

// ❌ BAD
import { BellIcon } from "@heroicons/react/24/outline"
```

## Colors
- **Tailwind color utilities only** — no raw hex values.
- `bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground` (shadcn semantic tokens) are fine.
- **Slate is the neutral color** — use `slate-*` for borders, muted backgrounds, secondary text.
- Do NOT use `zinc-*`, `gray-*`, or any raw `#hex` values.
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<p className="text-slate-500 border-slate-200">...</p>
<button className="bg-violet-600 text-white">...</button>

// ❌ BAD
<p style={{ color: "#6b7280" }}>...</p>
<div className="bg-zinc-100">...</div>
```

## Images & Avatars
- Always use `https://placehold.co/{w}x{h}` for placeholder images — never reference local files that don't exist.
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<img src="https://placehold.co/40x40" alt="user avatar" />

// ❌ BAD
<img src="/images/user.png" alt="user avatar" />
```

## Gradients
- Do NOT add gradients unless the user explicitly asks for them.

## Styling
- Tailwind CSS 4 utility classes only — no inline styles.
- Use shadcn/ui components for all base UI primitives (Button, Avatar, Badge, Card, etc.).
- Use prompt-kit components for all agentic/chat UI (PromptInput, Message, Loader, etc.).

## Layout
- All pages share the **AppShell** layout: left icon sidebar + main content area.
- Left alerts panel is shown on the **Home page only**.
- Keep page files under 300 lines — extract reusable pieces into `src/components/`.

## Typography
- Font: Inter (configured as `--font-sans` / `--font-inter` in globals.css).
- Headings: `font-semibold` or `font-bold`.
- Body: default weight.
- Muted/secondary text: `text-muted-foreground`.
- Code/data values: `font-mono` (JetBrains Mono).

## Code Quality
- All interactive pages must start with `"use client"`.
- No inline styles — Tailwind classes only.
- Keep component files under 150 lines; split into sub-components when needed.
- Add comments only for non-obvious logic — do not narrate what the code does.
